2500|$|On 7 January, Israel {{agreed to}} a three-hour <b>humanitarian</b> <b>truce,</b> {{allowing}} supplies and fuel into Gaza. The UN welcomed the move, but stated that round the clock assistance was required to meet the population humanitarian needs. The Human Rights Council expressed a similar position. The International Red Cross, United Nations and aid workers have reported intolerable conditions and a deepening humanitarian crisis in Gaza. The Red Cross has accused the Israeli military of failing [...] "to meet its obligation under international humanitarian law." ...|$|E
